            <li><strong>The repair cost is less than £400-500</strong> - As a general rule, if the repair costs less than 25% of a new boiler, it's usually worth doing</li>
            <li><strong>Parts are readily available</strong> - If genuine manufacturer parts are easy to obtain, repairs can be completed quickly</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>When Replacement Makes More Sense:</h3>
        <p>We'll typically recommend replacement when:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Your boiler is over 12-15 years old</strong> - Older boilers are less efficient, more prone to breakdowns, and parts can be expensive or unavailable</li>
