            <li><strong>The repair cost exceeds £600-800</strong> - At this point, the cost approaches a significant percentage of a new boiler's price</li>
            <li><strong>Parts are obsolete or very expensive</strong> - Discontinued boiler models can have parts that are hard to find or prohibitively expensive</li>
            <li><strong>Major component failure</strong> - If the heat exchanger or other major components fail, replacement often makes more financial sense</li>
            <li><strong>Your energy bills are high</strong> - Old, inefficient boilers can waste hundreds of pounds per year compared to modern A-rated models</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>We'll always explain your options clearly, including the likely costs of repair versus replacement, and help you make an informed decision that's right for your situation and budget. If replacement is the better option, we offer competitive <a href="/prices/">boiler installation prices</a> with extended warranties and finance options available.</p>
