        <h2>Power Flushing - Restore Your Heating System</h2>
        <p>Over time, sludge, rust, and debris can accumulate in your central heating system, reducing efficiency and causing problems like cold radiators, noisy boilers, and increased breakdowns. Power flushing is a deep-cleaning process that removes this buildup and restores your heating system to optimal performance.</p>
        
        <h3>Signs You Might Need a Power Flush:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Some radiators are cold at the bottom or have cold spots</li>
            <li>Radiators take a long time to heat up</li>
            <li>Boiler is making banging, clanking, or gurgling noises</li>
            <li>Your heating bills have increased without explanation</li>
            <li>System requires frequent topping up of pressure</li>
            <li>Boiler is frequently breaking down</li>
            <li>Radiator water is dark brown or black when bled</li>
            <li>System has not been power flushed in 5+ years</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>Benefits of Power Flushing:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Improved Efficiency</strong> - Clean systems heat your home faster and use less energy, reducing bills</li>
            <li><strong>Extend Boiler Life</strong> - Removing sludge prevents damage to your boiler's heat exchanger and pump</li>
            <li><strong>Better Heating</strong> - All radiators will heat evenly and quickly</li>
            <li><strong>Quieter Operation</strong> - Eliminates banging and kettling noises</li>
            <li><strong>Fewer Breakdowns</strong> - Clean systems are far less prone to component failures</li>
            <li><strong>Warranty Compliance</strong> - Many boiler warranties require a magnetic filter and clean system</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>Our power flushing service uses professional equipment to circulate cleaning chemicals through your entire heating system at high velocity, dislodging and removing sludge and debris. We then flush out all contaminants and add corrosion inhibitor to protect your system. The process typically takes 4-6 hours for an average home.</p>
        
        <p>We also install magnetic filters (such as MagnaClean or Fernox TF1) which continuously remove metal particles from your system, preventing future sludge buildup and protecting your boiler.</p>
