        <h2>Carbon Monoxide Safety - Protect Your Family</h2>
        <p>Carbon monoxide (CO) is a deadly, colorless, odorless gas produced when gas appliances burn fuel incompletely. Every year in the UK, approximately 60 people die from accidental carbon monoxide poisoning, and hundreds more are hospitalized. As heating professionals, we take carbon monoxide safety extremely seriously and educate all our customers about this invisible danger.</p>
        
        <h3>Symptoms of Carbon Monoxide Poisoning:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Headaches and dizziness</li>
            <li>Nausea and vomiting</li>
            <li>Tiredness and confusion</li>
            <li>Stomach pain</li>
            <li>Shortness of breath</li>
            <li>Collapse and loss of consciousness</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>The symptoms are similar to flu, but without a temperature. If multiple people in your home experience these symptoms, or if symptoms improve when you leave the house, carbon monoxide could be the cause.</p>
        
        <h3>Preventing Carbon Monoxide Poisoning:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Annual Boiler Service</strong> - Professional servicing checks combustion and flue integrity to ensure safe operation</li>
            <li><strong>Install CO Alarms</strong> - Place British Standard (BS EN 50291) approved CO alarms in rooms with gas appliances and in bedrooms</li>
            <li><strong>Use Gas Safe Engineers</strong> - Only allow Gas Safe registered engineers to install, service, or repair gas appliances</li>
            <li><strong>Look for Warning Signs</strong> - Yellow or orange pilot light (should be blue), sooty marks on appliances, excessive condensation</li>
            <li><strong>Ensure Ventilation</strong> - Never block vents, air bricks, or flues</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>During every service and repair, we test for carbon monoxide and inspect flues to ensure safe combustion. We strongly recommend all our customers install carbon monoxide alarms - they're inexpensive (£15-30) and could save your family's life. We can supply and fit audible CO alarms during our visit.</p>
        
        <p><strong>If your CO alarm sounds:</strong> Turn off all gas appliances, open windows and doors, evacuate everyone from the property, and call the National Gas Emergency Service on 0800 111 999 immediately.</p>
    </section>

